+# Step 5 Is Well Posed Because The Balanced Step-4 Dossier Leaves One Named Itinerary Repair
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` chain-step verdict with `INFERRED` dossier synthesis
+
+The completed balanced Step-4 dossier leaves one sharp outcome on the already
+frozen packet ledger.
+On the hostile side, the live anti-family `F_DT(delta, eta)` forces all three
+promoted candidates to fail, while `F_BM` functions only as the `A_live`
+filter check against vacuous static packets.
+On the friendly side, `F_SS(mu)` passes all three candidates and `F_SL(rho)`
+keeps the template-defect and leakage screens alive while leaving the
+itinerary ambiguous because the exact `t_next` trace is not uniformly fixed.
+
+After that symmetric anti/pro comparison,
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure` survives,
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` survives,
+and
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` remains one named ambiguity.
+
+Chain Step 5 is therefore well posed as one honest repair pass on the same
+packet object, window, thresholds, spectator partition, and sign / phase
+sheet, rather than as a fresh candidate search or a threshold-retuning pass.
+
+Filed from:
