+
+Status: `INFERRED` family classification on a `VERIFIED` frozen Step-4 sheet
+
+`F_SS(mu)` is the cleanest friendly family on the completed Step-4 ledger.
+On the fixed engineered-sign sparse-triad sheet, with the inherited normalized
+window, packet object, spectator partition, and pass/fail thresholds held
+fixed, all three promoted candidates pass:
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
+and
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`.
+
+This makes `F_SS(mu)` the only pro-circuit family currently recorded on disk
+that clears the full three-candidate menu on one explicit exact sheet.
+It is therefore the construction-facing positive witness for the balanced
+Step-4 dossier, not a license to retune other families, windows, sign sheets,
+or thresholds after the outcomes are known.
+
