+but
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` remains `ambiguous`.
+
+The recorded bottleneck is not raw spectator leakage.
+`F_SL(rho)` is already the small-leakage friendly test family, yet the exact
+`t_next` trace is not uniformly fixed across the family on the current local
+record.
+That sharpens the remaining weakness of the behavior-based candidate:
+the unresolved burden is event-trace rigidity on the frozen exact sheet rather
+than failure of the leakage ledger itself.
